text: was a town located in Oku District, Okayama Prefecture, Japan. As of 2003, the town had an estimated population of 12,431 and a density of 424.27 persons per km². The total area was 29.30 km². On November 1, 2004, Osafune, along with the towns of Oku and Ushimado (all from Oku District), was merged to create the city of Setouchi.
